Name: Cat scratch disease
Synonyms_List__c: Bartonellosis due to Bartonella henselae infection, Cat scratch fever
Disease_Description__c: A bacterial infection caused by Bartonella henselae. It is transmitted to humans from a scratch, bite, or lick from a cat. A blister or a bump appears on the skin following the scratch or bite. Subsequently, there is lymph node enlargement around the scratch or bite site. The lymph node enlargement most often occurs under the arm or the neck. Some patients experience fever, fatigue, headaches or sore throat as well.
